<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/geffrye-museum> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Located in London’s East End, the Museum of the Home depicts the quintessential style of English middle-class living rooms. Its collections of furniture, textiles, paintings and decorative arts are displayed in a series of period rooms from 1600 to the present day. Museum of the Home is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport ."@en .
